companyName: Credit Suisse FI Enhanced Europe 50 ETNs
description:
The investment seeks to provide a quarterly compounded 2x leveraged exposure to the STOXX® Europe 50 USD (Gross Return) Index (the “index”), reduced by the applicable ETN Fees.
 The ETNs are medium-term note, the return on which is linked to the performance of the index on a leveraged basis. The index is composed of the equity securities of 50 “blue-chip” European companies by free-float market capitalization selected from within the STOXX® Europe 600 Index (the “parent index”).
